SIMPLE: integrated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: integrated
<hw>integrated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed or united
into a whole.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> incorporate, incorporated, merged,
unified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Formed into a whole or introduced into another
entity; <as>as, an <ex>integrated</ex> Europe</as>. Opposite of
<ant>nonintegrated</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>coordinated</stype>, <stype>interconnected</stype>,
<stype>unified</stype>; <stype>embedded</stype>;
<stype>incorporated</stype>; <stype>tight-knit</stype>, <stype>tightly
knit</stype>]</p>

<p><q>a more closely <qex>integrated</qex> economic and political
system</q> <qau>Dwight D. Eisenhower</qau>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having different groups treated together as equals
in one group; <as>as, racially <ex>integrated</ex> schools</as>.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>co-ed, coeducational</stype>; <stype>desegrated,
nonsegregated, unsegregated</stype>; <stype>interracial</stype>;
<stype>mainstreamed</stype>] <see>Also See: <er>integrative</er>,
<er>joint</er>, <er>united</er>.</see> Antonym:
<ant>segregated</ant>.⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Resembling a living organism in organization or
development.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>organic</stype> (vs.
inorganic)]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> structured.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>combined. Opposite of
<ant>uncombined</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>having constituent parts mixed to form a single
unit. Opposite of <ant>unmixed</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>blended[2]</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> amalgamated, intermingled, mixed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>integrating</ent>⟦br⟧
